cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with a medical application of cancer detection in digital images, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques. The proposed algorithm uses machine learning (ML) techniques such as logistic regression and multiple instance learning (MIL) to model the probabilities of findings being marked as malignant. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also mentions the use of L1 regularization, which is a common technique in ML for feature selection and model sparsity. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, as it deals with the problem of multiple annotations from different experts. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another likely sub-category. 

Finally, the paper mentions experiments on a real-life computer aided diagnosis (CAD) problem for CXR CAD lung cancer detection, which involves medical imaging and analysis. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
